m is based on Code that differs from a Suggestion provided by GitHub Copilot\" which means that even if all filtering features are enabled, the defense obligations do not apply if the Customer makes any changes to the Suggestions. The underlying GitHub customer agreement also limits defense to GitHub products \\u201Cnot combined with anything else.\\u201D In case of lawsuit, GitHub would absolutely argue that the incorporation of a Suggestion into a customer\\u2019s code would be both a \\u201Cchange\\u201D and a combination. Finally, the Copilot terms explicitly say: \\u201CYou retain all responsibility for your code, including Suggestions you include in Your Code.\\u201D So taken together, what GitHub is really saying (albeit in a slightly tricky legal manner) is that \"if you enable all filtering features, we\\u2019ll defend you against a claim that our unmodified suggestions, used in a vacuum and not incorporated into your own code base, infringe.\\u201D This is obviously impractical, and Microsoft very much knows this - given the far reaching implications of such legal cases (if they do arise), even a company like Microsoft/GitHub will not want to be held liable for suits brought up against individual companies.']})})]})}}var G=x;function s(o,i){throw new Error(\"Expected \"+(i?\"component\":\"object\")+\" `\"+o+\"` to be defined: you likely forgot to import, pass, or provide it.\")}return H;})();\n;return Component;"},"authorDetails":[{"name":"Codeium Team","occupation":null,"company":null,"linkedin":null}],"prev":{"title":"Why did Microsoft Build VSCode? Turns out, GitHub Copilot.","date":"2023-06-13T07:00:00.000Z","tags":["industry"],"summary":"How Visual Studio Code does not have an even playing field when it comes to AI tooling.","images":["https://exafunction.github.io/public/hero/vscode_copilot/vscode_copilot_hero.png"],"authors":["default"],"layout":"PostSimple","dateStr":"June 13, 2023","slug":"why-did-microsoft-build-vscode-github-copilot","readingTim